value.value: A septum that divides a cavity or mass of tissue in a fruit and develops from an ovary septum.

definition.value: Annotations for Arabidopsis should go under fruit replum (PO:0025267), not under fruit septum. The partition between two fruit locules of an orange is a fruit septum. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to the specific type of fruit (PO:0009001), such as achene fruit (PO:0030107), berry fruit (PO:0030108), capsule fruit (PO:0030091), caryopsis fruit (PO:0030104), drupe fruit (PO:0030103), follicle fruit (PO:0030105), legume fruit (PO:0030100), nut fruit (PO:0030102), samara fruit (PO:0030099), schizocarp fruit (PO:0030098), silique fruit (PO:0030106), or their subclasses, depending on the species.

value.value: A collective plant structure (PO:0025497) composed of two or more cardinal organ parts (PO:0025001) that are part of adjacent plant organs (PO:0009008) and any associated portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007).

definition.value: A collective organ part structure is composed of parts of multiple organs, but no complete organs. The organ parts are often of the same type but may be of different types. Includes plant structures like a septum (PO:0000030) that consists of the walls of two fused carpels (PO:0009030) or a pseudostem (PO:0025248) that consist of multiple, overlapping leaf sheaths (PO:0020104). Unlike a collective plant organ structure (PO:0025007), a collective organ part structure does not contain any complete plant organs.

value.value: A locule (PO:0025263) that is a cavity in a fruit (PO:0009001) and develops from a plant ovary locule (PO:0025266).

definition.value: If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to the specific type of fruit (PO:0009001), such as achene fruit (PO:0030107), berry fruit (PO:0030108), capsule fruit (PO:0030091), caryopsis fruit (PO:0030104), drupe fruit (PO:0030103), follicle fruit (PO:0030105), legume fruit (PO:0030100), nut fruit (PO:0030102), samara fruit (PO:0030099), schizocarp fruit (PO:0030098), silique fruit (PO:0030106), or their subclasses, depending on the species.

value.value: A portion of ovary placenta tissue (PO:0020001) which divides a plant ovary (PO:0009072) into two or more chambers, and develops from contact of the placental tissue from opposite sides of the plant ovary early in gynoecium development (GO:0048467).

definition.value: An ovary replum develops along with the ovary and has no suture line in its center, while a true ovary septum (PO:0025262) is derived from the fusion two adjacent ovary walls. Common in Brassicaceae. Annotations for Arabidopsis should go here, and not under ovary septum.

value.value: A portion of shoot axis procambium gives rise to the primary vascular tissue of a stem.
A portion of shoot axis procambium gives rise to the primary vascular tissue of a branch.
A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that undergoes differentiation to form the primary vascular tissue (PO:0025408).

definition.value: May occur in an apical meristem or in a developing phyllome. Gives rise to the primary xylem and primary phloem. This term replaces PO:0006074.

value.value: A portion of procambium (PO:0025275) tissue that is part of a shoot system (PO:0009006).
A microsporangium that is part of a sporophyll and where the pollen grains develop and are located after they develop.

definition.value: A pollen sac is a microsporangium in seed plants. In angiosperms, a single, unfused pollen sac may contain an anther locule or several pollen sacs may fuse so they contain a single anther locule. If you are annotating to this structure for Zea mays or other grasses, please also add an annotation to the corresponding floret type. Choose the most specific term possible from: spikelet floret (PO:0009082), tassel floret (PO:0006310), lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of tassel (PO:0006313), lower floret of sessile spikelet of tassel (PO:0006315), upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of tassel (PO:0006314), upper floret of sessile spikelet of tassel (PO:0006316).

value.value: A scale leaf that grows from a rhizome.
A whole plant in the gametophyte development stage (PO:0028003) that produces only plant egg cells (PO:0020094).

definition.value: Megagametophytes in bryophytes only produce egg cells, but do not develop from megaspores, because there is no heterospory in bryophytes. In some pteridophytes, megagametophytes develop from megaspores. In angiosperms, Gnetum, and Weltwischia, the megagametophyte is greatly reduced. The megagametophyte in angiosperms is an embryo sac.

value.value: A whole plant (PO:0000003) in the gametophyte development stage (PO:0028003) that produces plant sperm cells (PO:0000084).

definition.value: The microgametophyte in bryophytes only produce sperm cells, but do not develop from microspores, because there is no heterospory in bryophytes. In seed plants the male gametophyte is reduced to a pollen grain.

value.value: A microgametophyte (PO:0025280) that develops from a microspore (PO:0020048) is located in a pollen sac (PO:0025277).
A megagametophyte (PO:0025279) that has as parts one or more archegonia (PO:0025126).

definition.value: Megagametophytes in bryophytes only produce egg cells, but do not develop from megaspores, because there is no heterospory in bryophytes. In some pteridophytes, megagametophytes develop from megaspores.

value.value: A microgametophyte (PO:0025280) that has as parts one or more antheridia (PO:0025125).

definition.value: Microgametophytes in bryophytes only produce sperm cells, but do not develop from microspores, because there is no heterospory in bryophytes. In some pteridophytes, microgametophytes develop from microspores.

value.value: A sporophyte meristematic apical cell that is part of a plant embryo and is the uppermost cell formed after the first division of a zygote.

definition.value: The zygote divides to form an embryo apical cell and an embryo basal cell.

value.value: A parenchyma cell that is part of a plant callus.
A coleoptile (PO:0020033) that is part of a plant embryo (PO:0009009).
A coleoptile (PO:0020033) that is part of a seedling (PO:0008037).

definition.value: A seedling coleoptile develops from an embryo coleoptile (PO:0025286).

value.value: A coleorhiza (PO:0020034) that is part of a plant embryo (PO:0009009).
A coleorhiza (PO:0020034) that is part of a seedling (PO:0008037).

definition.value: Develops from an embryo coleorhiza (PO:0025288).

value.value: A hypocotyl (PO:0020100) that is part of a plant embryo axis (PO:0019018).
A hypocotyl (PO:0020100) that is part of a seedling (PO:0008037).

definition.value: Develops from an embryo hypocotyl (PO:0025290). This term should only be used for seed plants.

value.value: An epicotyl (PO:0020035) that is part of a plant embryo (PO:0009009).
An epicotyl (PO:0020035) that is part of a seedling (PO:0008037).

definition.value: Develops from an embryo epicotyl (PO:0025292).

value.value: A mesocotyl (PO:0020037) that is part of a plant embryo (PO:0009009).
A mesocotyl (PO:0020037) that develops from an embryo mesocotyl (PO:0025294) and is part of a seedling (PO:0008037).

definition.value: A seedling mesocotyl is an elongation of an embryo mesocotyl (PO:0025294) and is part of a seedling (PO:0008037)..

value.value: A radicle (PO:0020031) that is part of a plant embryo (PO:0009009).

definition.value: May eventually develop into the root system (PO:0025025)  of an adult plant. Sometimes is abortive.

value.value: A radicle (PO:0020031) that is part of a seedling (PO:0008037).

definition.value: Develops from an embryo radicle (PO:0025296). May develop into the root system (PO:0025025) of an adult plant.

value.value: A collective organ part structure that is the apical part of a circumsessile capsular fruit that separates from the rest of the capsule during dehiscence.

definition.value: Develops from the apical portion of a gynoecium, and is commonly found as part of the fruit of species of Myrtaceae, such as Eucalyptus spp. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to the specific type of fruit (PO:0009001), such as achene fruit (PO:0030107), berry fruit (PO:0030108), capsule fruit (PO:0030091), caryopsis fruit (PO:0030104), drupe fruit (PO:0030103), follicle fruit (PO:0030105), legume fruit (PO:0030100), nut fruit (PO:0030102), samara fruit (PO:0030099), schizocarp fruit (PO:0030098), silique fruit (PO:0030106), or their subclasses, depending on the species.

value.value: A hypocotyl-root junction (PO:0004724) that is part of an plant embryo axis (PO:0019018).
A hypocotyl-root junction (PO:0004724) that develops from an embryo hypocotyl-root junction (PO:0025300) and is part of a seedling (PO:0008037).

definition.value: Part of a seedling (PO:0008037).

value.value: A plant embryo (PO:0009009) that arises from previously differentiated somatic cells, rather than from fused gametes, i.e. the plant zygote (PO:0000423).

definition.value: Somatic plant embryos may arise where embryos normally would not arise as a product of apomixis. They may occur on the edges of leaves on some species of Kalanchoe or some ferns.

value.value: A plant embryo (PO:0009009) that forms as a result of the fusion of gametes.
A zygotic plant embryo that is grown or maintained in vitro.
A cultured somatic plant embryo that develops from isolated microspores.
A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) that is composed of the outer layers of a sporangium (PO:0025094) and bounds the archesporium (PO:0030074) or plant spores (PO:0025017).

definition.value: May have multiple layers such as exothecium, endothecium and tapetum. Early in development, the sporangium wall bounds the archesporium. Later, after spores develop from the archesporium, it bounds the spore or spores.

value.value: A sporangium wall (PO:0025306) that is part of a microsporangium (PO:0025202).
A sporangium wall that is part of a megasporangium.
A sporangium wall endothecium (PO:0030049) that is part of a microsporangium wall (PO:0025307).
A sporangium wall endothecium (PO:0030049) that is part of a megasporangium wall.
A portion of exothecium (PO:0030073) that is part of a microsporangium wall (PO:0025307).
A portion of exothecium (PO:0030073) that is part of a megasporangium wall (PO:0025308).
A portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059) that is the inner-most layer of a sporangium wall (PO:0025306).

definition.value: May function in providing nutrition to developing sporocytes or pollen. May have one or more layers of cells. May break down as spores mature. A tapetum does not develop in some plants, such as Psilotum. In angiosperms, the tapetum develops from one of the parietal layers. In non-seed plants, the tapetum may develop from the outer cells of archesporium or from the inner-most layer of the sporangium wall. The tapetum may be one of two types ameboid or secretory/glandular.

value.value: An tapetum (PO:0025313) that is part of a microsporangium wall (PO:0025307).
A tapetum (PO:0025313) that is part of a megasporangium wall (PO:0025308).
A multicellular trichome (PO:0025162) that has as parts a long terminal cell atop a basal stalk and grows in a leaf axil (PO:0009023).

definition.value: Found in monocots and mosses. The basal stalk may contain one or more cells.

value.value: A trichome cell (PO:0008030) that is the long terminal cell of an axillary hair (PO:0008030).
A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is the basal part of an axillary hair (PO:0025316), below the axillary hair terminal cell (PO:0025317).

definition.value: Consists of two or more plant cells.

value.value: A trichome cell (PO:0008030) that is part of a base of an axillary hair (PO:0025316).
